  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/31dd261fdb32d938fbb615557413aba0116c4f68" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -4.171ex; width:51.381ex; height:9.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle L_{y}={\begin{bmatrix}+1/2&amp;0&amp;-1/2\end{bmatrix}}L\quad {\text{and}}\quad L_{x}={\begin{bmatrix}+1/2\\0\\-1/2\end{bmatrix}}L.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>The well-known and earlier <a href="/wiki/Sobel_operator" title="Sobel operator">Sobel operator</a> is based on the following filters:
</p>
